HB238 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2 To make appropriations for the support, maintenance and
3 development of public education in Alabama, for debt service,
4 and for capital outlay for the fiscal year ending September
5 30, 2027.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
7 Section 1. There is hereby appropriated for the support
8 of public education in Alabama for the fiscal year ending
9 September 30, 2027, for debt service, and for capital outlay
10 to be paid out of funds specified in subsection (a) of Section
11 2 of this act and the amounts specified in subsections (a),
12 (b), (c), (d), and (e) of Section 3 of this act. For the
13 purpose specified in subsection (b) of Section 2 of this act,
14 amounts are shown by programmatic area and the total for all
15 programs is shown so as to include estimated sources of funds
16 other than those listed in subsection (a) of Section 2 of this
17 act. For the purpose of this act, "ETF" shall mean the
18 Education Trust Fund and "Federal and Local Funds" shall mean
19 all gifts, grants, contributions, or entitlements, including
20 grants by the Congress of the United States, municipalities or
21 counties.
22 Section 2. (a) The appropriations provided for in this
23 act shall be paid from funds in the State Treasury to the
24 credit of the Education Trust Fund, Alabama Peace Officers'
25 Standards and Training Fund, Alabama Head and Spinal Cord
26 Injury Trust Fund, Driver Education and Training Fund, Special
27 Education Catastrophic Fund, Public School Fund and other
Page 1

Education Catastrophic Fund, Public School Fund and other
HB238 Enrolled
28 listed funds and are hereby made for the support of public
29 education in Alabama for the fiscal year ending September 30,
30 2027, and the appropriations herein made shall be subject to
31 the provisions, terms, conditions and limitations of the
32 Budget and Financial Control Act (Code of Alabama 1975,
33 Sections 41-4-80 et seq.), the provisions of the Budget
34 Management Act of 1976 (Code of Alabama 1975, Sections 41-19-1
35 et seq.), and shall be in the amounts hereinafter specified.
36 (b) Amounts shown hereinunder the columns "Other Funds"
37 and "Total" are as set forth for the purpose of establishing
38 amounts estimated to be available by programmatic area from
39 sources other than those listed in subsection (a) of this
40 Section 2, in order, upon consideration of such other funds so
41 estimated to be available, to promote the accountability for
42 an efficient use of funds available, and the same are hereby
43 appropriated by the Legislature. Provided, however, that
44 regardless of the ending date of any pay period which has been
45 or may be established by the Legislature for the payment of
46 salaries of state employees, the entire payment due shall be
47 made from the fiscal year's appropriation in which the pay
48 date falls.
49 (c) All appropriations made in Section 3 shall be at
50 the program level. Any directed expenditure of funds below a
51 program shall be from funds appropriated for the program.
