121 The Council on the Arts may award grants from the facilities grant program
122 for projects that build, renovate, restore, preserve, or enhance arts
123 facilities in Alabama, including performing arts centers, art museums and
124 galleries, multi-purpose arts centers, artist residency facilities, and
125 outdoor performance venues. The Council on the Arts shall emphasize rural
126 assistance with grants, with a preference for entities not receiving grants
127 in the prior year. Eligible entities include: (i) 501(c) (3) nonprofit arts
128 organizations chartered in Alabama, active and in good standing with the
129 Internal Revenue Service and the council; or (ii) an entity of local
130 government. Grant amounts shall not exceed $100,000 to any one entity, with
131 the first two grants being reserved for the Arts Council of the Trussville
132 Area Theater for $75,000 and the Carnegie Visual Arts Center for $100,000.
