177 The funds appropriated for Workforce Development are to be expended for those costs
178 incurred by the State in honoring commitments to pay workforce development costs,
179 including services and other assistance and expenses of recruitment and training of
180 a company's workforce, that are undertaken to induce companies to locate and expand
181 their operations in Alabama (described hereinafter as a "Project") and to develop
182 and implement training, placement and recruitment programs that will improve
183 development and expand the State's workforce. Such costs include, but are not
184 limited to: (i) AIDT operating costs directly related to a Project; (ii) wages and
185 benefits for trainers engaged by AIDT for the purpose of a Project; (iii) costs
186 which the State has agreed to pay under the terms of a Project Agreement with a
187 company that are necessary and reasonable charges incurred by the company or its
188 affiliates for personnel providing training to the company's employees, whether
189 those trainers are employees of the company or its vendors or suppliers, including
190 wages, benefits and travel (domestic and, when necessary, international); (iv) any
191 necessary materials, equipment, manuals, or other relevant training materials; (v)
192 the costs incurred for purchasing or repairing or replacing training tools and
193 equipment; (vi) costs incurred for the purchase or construction and maintenance of
194 training facilities; (vii) travel expenses for prospective and current employees and
195 trainees, including travel, food, lodging, relocation, and other costs necessary and
196 reasonable to enable the company to secure a qualified workforce; and (viii) outside
197 training fees. The above funds appropriated for Workforce Development shall be
198 expended primarily for the training of Alabama residents. It is further the intent
199 that contracts with vendors to provide workforce training shall be inclusive and
200 reflect the racial and gender diversity of the State. The Secretary of the
201 Department of Commerce shall report semi-annually to the Chairs of the Senate
202 Committee on Finance and Taxation-Education, the House Ways and Means-Education
203 Committee, the Finance Director, and the Legislative Fiscal Officer any funds
204 allocated for workforce training. Such report shall include a summary of the persons
205 trained and the vendors providing the training. The report shall contain information
206 including the residence, race and gender of the persons trained and of the principal
207 or majority owner of the firm or business contracted with to provide the training
208 services.
