362 Scholarship Program
363 The Board of Trustees of the Alabama Community College System, in consultation
364 with the Alabama Industrial Development and Training Institute, shall
365 establish qualifications for the award of scholarships to high school students
366 and adults enrolled in a state educational program relating to the automotive
367 manufacturing industry and shall further provide for the implementation and
368 administration of the scholarships. Scholarship recipients shall be selected
369 by the Board, in consultation with a scholarship committee, comprised of
370 members of the Board of Directors of the Alabama Automotive Manufacturers
371 Association, from applications submitted to the association. The Board shall
372 file a report with the Chairs of the Senate Committee on Finance and
373 Taxation-Education, the House Ways and Means-Education Committee, the
374 Legislative Fiscal Officer, and the Finance Director on September 30, 2027
375 regarding the total number of scholarships awarded for the Fall term of the
376 2026-2027 academic year and the institution attended by the scholarship
377 recipients. The report shall also include the name of each scholarship
378 recipient and the number of years the recipient has received a scholarship.
