1054 benefit costs for Certified Academic Language Therapists (CALT) and other
1055 costs of the program. Supplement amounts will be determined by the
1056 availability of funds based on the number of CALT Teachers. The state of
1057 Alabama will provide an annual supplement of $5,000 to any CALT that is
1058 employed full-time in a public K-12 school system or public independent
1059 school and is properly certified by the state of Alabama. The existing
1060 eligibility criteria will apply: (a) CALTs employed on less than a full-time
1061 contract on October 1 will receive a pro-rata share of the salary
1062 supplement. (b) CALTs employed full-time after October 1 will receive a
1063 pro-rata share of the salary supplement. (c) Any CALT employed full-time in
1064 Alabama and properly certified by the state of Alabama will receive the
1065 annual salary stipend. (d) CALTs employed as a substitute are not eligible
1066 for the salary supplement. (e) CALTs who are on leave of absence for more
1067 than half a school year will receive a prorated amount based on the number
1068 of months worked during the school year. (f) CALTs will receive the salary
1069 supplement each year of the valid period of the CALT credentials unless the
1070 Alabama Legislature declines to make the annual appropriation. (g) CALTs
1071 must maintain their CALT credentials in order to continue receiving the
1072 salary supplement. (h) CALTs employed in the final year of their CALT
1073 credentials valid period will receive a prorated amount based on the number
1074 of months worked covered in that valid period. (i) CALTs who leave after
1075 October 1 will be eligible for a prorated amount based on the months served.
1076 (j) CALTs must remain employed with a public K-12 Local Board of Education
1077 school system or public independent school to continue receiving the salary
1078 supplement.
