1083 Of the above appropriation, $17,200,000 shall be expended for the Alabama
1084 Summer and Afterschool Program (ASAP) grants program with the objective of
1085 reducing the achievement gap in students who are not proficient in reading
1086 and/or math.
1087 The State Superintendent of Education shall administer the grants process.
1088 Grants shall be awarded to a) local education agencies, municipalities, and
1089 not-for-profit organizations for summer and afterschool programs that
1090 provide direct services and b) to entities that provide support to summer
1091 and after-school programs. Afterschool programs shall be guided by the
1092 Alabama Afterschool Quality Standards; summer programs shall be guided by
1093 the "Final Report and Recommendations" of the Alabama Campaign for
1094 Grade-Level Reading, Pages 81-92.
1095 Data on student and program outcomes shall be collected and used to inform a
1096 continuous improvement process. A report shall be provided to the
1097 Legislature listing grantees and summarizing outcomes.
1098 The intent of the Legislature is to increase access to evidence-based,
1099 high-quality summer and afterschool programming, to build a diverse delivery
1100 model of providers, and to foster collaboration between local education
1101 agencies and community-based organizations. The goal is to award at least
1102 60% of the funding to nonprofit, community based organizations or
1103 partnerships between community-based organizations and local education
1104 agencies.
