1518 The above appropriation includes funds to pay salary supplements and related
1519 benefit costs for Nationally Board-Certified Teachers (NBCT) and other costs
1520 of the program. Supplement amounts will be determined by the availability of
1521 funds based on the number of National Board Certified Teachers. (1) The
1522 state of Alabama will provide an annual supplement of $5,000 to any NBCT
1523 that is employed full-time in a public K-12 school and is properly certified
1524 by the state of Alabama. The existing eligibility criteria will apply: (a)
1525 NBCTs employed on a less than full-time contract on October 1 will receive a
1526 pro-rata share of the salary supplement. (b) NBCTs employed full-time after
1527 October 1 will receive a pro-rata share of the salary supplement. (c) NBCTs
1528 who earn National Board Certification in another state and are teaching
1529 full-time in Alabama on October 1 and are properly certified by the state of
1530 Alabama will receive the annual salary stipend. (d) NBCTs employed as a
1531 substitute are not eligible for the salary supplement. (e) NBCTs who are on
1532 leave of absence for more than half a school year will receive a prorated
1533 amount based on the number of months worked during the school year. (f)
1534 NBCTs will receive the salary supplement each year of the valid period of
1535 the certificate unless the Alabama Legislature declines to make the annual
1536 appropriation. (g) NBCTs must renew their certificate by the year of the
1537 certificate's expiration in order to continue receiving the salary
1538 supplement. (h) NBCTs employed in the final year of the certificate valid
