1920 The Retain Alabama project will provide digital marketing strategies
1921 targeting soon-to-be college graduates, promotional materials about Alabama
1922 and career opportunities, and other strategies to retain Alabama College
1923 graduates initiated by the Executive Director in collaboration and
1924 coordination with Innovate Alabama. The Retention Initiative would help
1925 retain Alabama College graduates by: (1) Identifying internships, co-op
1926 opportunities, and entry-level jobs at emerging companies and established
1927 companies in Alabama; (2) Partnering with Alabama colleges and universities
1928 to promote these career opportunities to Alabama college students throughout
1929 the State; and (3) Creating opportunities for Alabama college students to
1930 learn more about communities throughout Alabama, while also engaging with
1931 other students to create a cohort environment.
