2051 To be distributed as grants to monuments to commemorate historical events
2052 and places, historical skills centers, cultural heritage parks, historic
2053 sites, commissions, boards, agencies, and authorities that are not owned,
2054 operated, or otherwise under the control of the Alabama Historical
2055 Commission or other state agencies. Grants will be awarded to entities that
2056 reflect a historical education-based mission and concentrate on historical
2057 educational programming. Preference shall be given to: (1) any property
2058 constructed prior to 1840 that is listed in or eligible for the National
2059 Register of Historic Places and that are publicly owned and accessible to
2060 the public; or (2) any property in Alabama built in 1943 or before, and is
2061 listed in or eligible for the National Register of Historic Places or any
2062 property built after 1943 that significantly contributed to the civil rights
2063 movement. The first three grants shall be reserved for Old State Bank for
2064 $200,000, Hartselle Historical Depot for $100,000, and Mt. Pinson
